name: integer_i8_one
description: |
  One is a baseline i8 operand for boundary arithmetic. Adding it to the maximum
  overflows, subtracting it from the minimum underflows, and dividing it by zero
  exercises integer divide-by-zero handling. These pairings also catch checks
  that are accidentally applied after an overflowing operation.
format: hex
decode-as: i8
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i8"
  - "one"
  - "overflow"
  - "underflow"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
01 # 1
